At the time of Kennedy's inauguration Radziwill was living in London, married to Prince Stanisław Albrecht Radziwill. and had a son Anthony and daughter Christina.Despite being married though, Radziwill had a very close relationship with Greek shipping magnate Aristotle Onasis.The Kennedys did not approve of this relationship, and according to Vanity Fair President Kennedy encouraged Jackie to join her sister on Onasis' yacht in the Mediterranean during the summer of 1963 to convince her not to marry the man.Five years later, after the death of her husband, Onassis married Jackie on Skorpios, a private island he owned off of Greece.Jackie did not tell her sister about the wedding, with Onassis instead the one who informed Radziwill.'He begged me to come to the wedding,' she said, which she did in fact agree to do despite their past.   





 Relief: says that she felt 'free' after he was assassinated (President Kennedy and Jackie in their motorcade just before the shooting)   





 Close: Radziwill was very close to Aristotle Onassis for years, despite being married (pair above in September 1963)  





 Not sisterly: Jackie would later go on to marry her sister's lover Onassis (above in 1968)Radziwill is said to have called her closest friend at the time, writer, Truman Capote, and said: 'How could she do this to me!'She publicly put on a brave face however and met a new friend at the wedding, famed photographer Peter Beard. He would later move into her Manhattan apartment and the two began to spend time in the Hamptons, like Radziwill had done as a child.It was while with Beart that Radziwill became friends with the likes of Andy Warhol and laid the groundwork for the film Grey Gardens, about her cousins Big Edie and Little Edie Beale.It was 1972 and Radziwill wanted to make a documentary about growing up in the Hamptons that would include the Beales, and filmmakers David and Albert Maysles were brought on to the project.The focus changed however when it was discovered the two women were living in filth inside their East Hampton mansion, and that the house was in danger of being condemned.Radziwilll said it was her that came in and cleaned up, not her sister as it is widely reported, and was able to help the women keep the home.   





 Rave: 'She has that feminine quality that’s hard to put your finger on. Men just fell at her feet. There is an elegant casualness that I don’t think I’ve seen since,' said Radziwill's daughter-in-law Carole (above in 2014)






Onassis would eventually divorce Jackie but died in 1975 before it was finalized, leaving her a very wealthy woman. Radziwill would also divorce her husband after 15 years of marriage in 1974.Jackie never married again, and in 1994 died of cancer. Radziwill still lives in New York City, as does her daughter Anna.Her son Anthony tragically died of cancer in 1999, and his widow, Carole Radziwill, is now a cast member on the Bravo show Real Housewives of New York.When asked to describe her mother-in-law by Vanity Fair, Carole said; 'She has that feminine quality that’s hard to put your finger on. Men just fell at her feet. There is an elegant casualness that I don’t think I’ve seen since.'She also said that when she first married Anthony, many asked Carole if she was a Kennedy. 'I have to correct people when they say, "Oh, you’re married into the Kennedy family,"' she said. '"No, I married into the Radziwill family." It was a point of honor for me.' 


Read more:

The Complicated Sisterhood of Jackie Kennedy and Lee Radziwill | Vanity Fair





